<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Motley" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Motley,</orth> 1) the particoloured dress of domestic fools or jesters: <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.34" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.34" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 34</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.160" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 160</bibl>. Adjectively: <cit><quote>a m. fool,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 13</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 13</bibl> <cit><quote>a m. coat,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 13</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 13</bibl>.<lb />2) a fool: <cit><quote>made myself a m. to the view,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 110.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 110, 2</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>will you be married, m.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 3, 79</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>